casebody.data:
Sam PERRONE and Gasper Perrone, v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 7637. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit Oct. 15, 1937. Donald B. Frederick, of Detroit, Mich., for appellants. John C. Lehr, of Detroit, Mich., for the United States.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal in this cause be, and the same is, dismissed, pursuant to stipulation of counsel.

Appeal dismissed.
